Troops of 1 Division, Nigerian Army under Operation Whirl Punch have eliminated five bandits including a notorious bandit from Zamfara identified as Sani Danbuzuwa.   This was contained in a press release issued Thursday in Kaduna by the Deputy Director, 1 Division Army Public Relations, Colonel Muhammad Dole.  He regrettably noted that one soldier was killed during the pursuit of the bandits in Kwuyambana forest in Zamfara State while two others were injured adding, "The wounded soldiers were evacuated and they are responding to treatment in military hospital in Kaduna."  He said, "The soldiers were responding to a distress call about an armed robbery along Birnin Gwari - Funtua road where they were ambushed by suspected bandits. However, they fought their way and overpowered the bandits, who hastily withdrew into Kwuyambana forest in Zamfara State.  "After thorough searched of the ambush area, the following items were recovered, 1 x AK47 rifle, 3 x magazines, 87 rounds of 7.62mm (special), 1 x G3 rifle, 4 x magazines and 61 rounds of 7.62mm (NATO).  "Likewise, a wanted vicious kidnapper and expert in negotiations for ransom, called Yinusa Suleiman from Sambuwa village was apprehended by troops on 14 August 2018. He is currently assisting the security operatives in further investigations."  He assured the committed and determined of troops to ensure security and safe passage to all commuters along highways of Kaduna - Abuja and Kaduna - Birnin Gwari roads as well as adjoining towns and villages.   See recovered arms and ammunition from bandits below: 